dismissalText.commentary: Glenn Maxwell c du Plessis b Morkel 29 (19b 5x4 0x6 23m) SR: 152.63

dismissalComment.html: it's full this time and it's worked, taken at mid-off! Maxwell made room, got it full and wanted to clear mid-off with a lofted drive but Faf did well to dive forward and to his left for a good low catch. They are checking with the third umpire if it was taken cleanly, it has. And a part of Morkel's heel was marginally inside the crease or it would have been a no ball

dismissalText.commentary: AB de Villiers run out (sub [SPD Smith]) 80 (76b 4x4 1x6 138m) SR: 105.26

dismissalComment.html: oh, there's a run out and AB's gone! Steyn defended the short ball on the off side towards point, he took a step out but then said no for the single. It's too late because AB is already halfway down the track, Steven Smith (in for Clarke) runs from point, picks the ball and sends in the underarm throw at the non-striker's end, AB is well outside the crease. Big Blow for SA

dismissalText.commentary: David Miller c Marsh b Coulter-Nile 65 (65b 5x4 1x6 83m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: the bowling change as done it, Miller is gone and this strong stand is broken! the length delivery was angled in towards the pads, Miller looked to flick it towards cow corner but played the shot early and even though he looked towards wide long on, the ball went straight to mid on. Marsh takes a few steps back to complete the catch and 126-run stand is broken

three down, SA! Short ball outside off, Behardien pulled it but didn't middle it, looked like it took a chunk of the top of the bat and went high towards deep midwicket where Finch ran to his left to pouch it

dismissalComment.html: stifled appeal for caught behind as it was another bouncer! McLaren took evasive action while trying to defend it as the ball angled in, and Bailey reviews it. The third umpire says: "Looks like it has come off the shoulder, can we zoom in please." Another angle shows there might be a glove, third umpire wants to see the Hotspot and the crowd erupts seeing it on the big screen. Third umpire says there's glove on it, confirmed by Hotspot and he conveys it to the on-field umpire. McLaren gone for a duck
one more! Steyn makes room to cut the incoming delivery on the off side, but it comes in too sharply after bouncing and takes a thin outside edge as Wade dives to his left to catch it with both hands

145kph, edged and that's gone, MJ strikes! It was on back of length outside off, QDK only pushed at it away from the body without any footwork, the ball wasn't close to him and and the outside edge went for an easy catch to the keeper

that's an unusual shot from Amla and he's fallen to MJ too! It was slightly back of length and close to off, Amla made room and stayed low to cut it fine, maybe towards third man, but only found a thick outside edge and Wade pouched another catch. Openers back in the pavilion

dismissalText.commentary: Imran Tahir c Warner b Maxwell 22 (22b 4x4 0x6 29m) SR: 100

commentPreTextItems.html: Hassam: "Tail ender scores more runs than middle. I guess there is something for batsman as well. SA did not capitalize it."

commentTextItems.html: the last wicket has fallen, he came down the track and lofted the fullish delivery straight down to long-off where Warner took the catch

commentPostTextItems.html: 7.50pm So Australia go 1-0 up with a 32-run win even though the margin could have been bigger. SA were well on track with that partnership between de Villiers and Miller, and they had hopes even after Miller fell. But AB's run out was the turning point and the short-ball barrage from Coulter-Nile and Hazlewood was outstanding.
Sriniwas: "I missed Duminy a lot today. Because inadvertently, he was he one who use to hold up the middle and tail order, whenever the top order failed"
Charlie: "The old saying rings true "catches win matches""

Nathan Coulter-Nile is the Man of the Match: Mitch was bowling rockets so bowling was easier. Our first game back in the summer and were slightly lacklustre, sloppy in the field but it turned out pretty well. Very good knock form George Bailey and it was a pretty good wicket. The WACA pitch was a bit slower than usual.

AB de Villiers: We didn't do well in all three depts. Our bowling was good at times but no consistency and we lost wickets at the wrong time. Very disappointing. We'll have to fix our mistakes for the second game. I'm not sure about the team changes right now, we'll see that tomorrow. [Run out with Steyn] has happened before, not our first time. He wasn't sure and I was so he sent me back, no hard feelings.

George Bailey: Reasonably happy with our bowling, taking early wickets was important. It would have been nice to finish it earlier but pretty happy with out bowling and fielding. Hope I get some sort of luck for the rest of my career as well after those dropped catches. 250 I think was what were looking at and then we kept adding, Maxi was in the shed and so was Coulter-Nile, all good strikers of the ball. Nathan maybe thought our fielding was sloppy because he saw much more. I was too involved with the captaincy and we challenged ourselves after the second drinks break.
That's all we have from the first ODI, join us again on Sunday at the same time for the match on the same ground. Till then, goodbye!

commentTextItems.html: that's gone high in the air towards point after Tahir lofted the ball from outside off but it falls short again for the fielder who was running in
and another one - Tahir hooks the short ball and a top edge flies over the keeper's head for four
four more! Back of length outside the off stump, Tahir stays back and crunches it in the gap on the off side for four
short ball this time and he pulls it straight to deep midwicket
outside off again, punched down the ground to mid off

commentPreTextItems.html: Chim: "2rd Highest partnership in the innings already ! "

commentTextItems.html: length delivery outside the off stump, pushed towards cover
full outside off, smashed down the ground to long on who takes it after a bounce
flighted and slower on middle stump, swept to deep backward square leg for one
fuller on the stumps, tucked to short fine leg
sweeps the ball that's turning in from outside off, it goes fine and even beats short fine leg for four
he turns this one into Morkel who pushes the ball to long on

commentPreTextItems.html: 51 from 24, one wicket to go, here's Maxwell

commentTextItems.html: charges down the track and lofts it to long on for one, falls well short
makes room and cuts the ball to third man for one
bouncer angled in again, Tahir tries to play the ramp shot but doesn't connect
back of length and angled in, Tahir defends off the back foot
bouncer for Tahir, he ducks under it
another short ball, pulled to square leg for one
short ball to Morkel and he swats it on the leg side off the back foot for four
length delivery on the off side, Tahir defends on the leg side
